# FlyNow HAOS deployment

Full deployment reference: [.planning/reference/HAOS-DEPLOYMENT.md](../../.planning/reference/HAOS-DEPLOYMENT.md)

## Quick facts

- **SSH:** `miro@192.168.68.111:22` (standard port 22, NOT 22222)
- **Key:** `~/.ssh/id_ed25519_flynow` (no passphrase)
- **Sudo:** NOPASSWD on `miro`; `/config` is root-owned — use `sudo` for writes
- **HA Core:** 2026.4.3, Python 3.12.13, HACS 2.0.5
- **`ha` CLI does NOT work** from this SSH session (no supervisor token) — restart HA via UI

## Deploy targets

| Source | HAOS path |
|---|---|
| `custom_components/flynow/` | `/config/custom_components/flynow/` |
| `lovelace/flynow-card/dist/` | `/config/www/flynow-card/` (served at `/local/flynow-card/flynow-card.js`) |

**Don't use `/config/www/community/`** — that's HACS-managed.

## Deploy command (tar over SSH; rsync unavailable on dev machine)

```bash
tar --exclude='__pycache__' --exclude='*.pyc' --exclude='.ruff_cache' --exclude='.mypy_cache' \
  -czf - -C custom_components flynow \
  | ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_flynow -p 22 miro@192.168.68.111 \
    "sudo tar xzf - -C /config/custom_components/"
```

After Python changes: user must restart HA via Settings → System → Restart Home Assistant.

